article.headline: N. Colorado 88, Johnson &amp, Wales, Colo. 67
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Will Figures scored 22 points and Northern Colorado had little trouble defeating Johnson & Wales, Colo., 88-67 on Tuesday night. Connor Osborne added 11 points and seven rebounds for the Bears (23-6), who won their third straight. Northern Colorado is one victory from matching the school record for most wins in a season. The Bears went 24-6 in 1988-89. Ethan Fisher led Johnson & Wales (15-13), an NAIA Division II school, with 19 points. Andrew Baker had 14 points for the Wildcats. The game was a tuneup for Northern Colorado's regular season finale Saturday at Sacramento State. A win would ensure the Bears the No. 2 seed in the upcoming Big Sky tournament.
